<subSubSection pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="58.[189,1398,1917,2027]" box="[189,324,1917,1943]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,1917,1943]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1917,1943]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="58.[189,1398,1917,2027]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
The epithet 'hutan' means 'forest' in Bahasa 
<collectingCountry box="[713,827,1964,1990]" name="Indonesia" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[887,995,1964,1990]" name="Malaysia" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
alluding to the occurrence of this species in the forest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
